cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.MA, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the performance of a specific LPWAN technology (LoRaWAN) in terms of inter-network interference and its scalability potential. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the effect of modulation coding schemes (data rates) on the probability of successful packet delivery. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible category as the paper may touch upon security issues related to inter-network interference. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the impact of inter-network interference on the coordination and communication between multiple agents in a network. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the impact of inter-network interference on the control and stability of a system.
